This looks OK to me, but I think @semorrison or @fgdorais should check this matches their expectations.
All changes here look good to me. Eric's proposed edit also looks good.

Since this takes in a Fin, would this be better as
```suggestion
  toFun i := x[Fin.cast (Nat.succ_pred_eq_of_pos <| List.length_pos.mpr x_ne_nil) i]
```
or similar?
I guess the same question arises here; should `a[i.cast h]` be preferred to `a[i]'(by rw [h]; exact i.2)`?

I've encountered some awkwardness with `a[i]'(h)` when `i` is `Fin _` and `h` is nontrivial. I expect this to be fixed sooner than later but, since we happen to be in the present, I think `Fin.cast` has better support.
My main concern is that `Finc.cast` is not the simp normal form here.
That is a very legitimate concern. My personal opinion is that the simp normal form of `a[i]'(h)` is still fluid in some cases so it's a gamble either way.
